{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/astronomykit\/moonphases"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"Moon Phases","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"AstronomyKit"}]},"abstract":[{"text":"Calculate moon phases, quarters, libration, and lunar nodes.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/MoonPhases","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Moon","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type provides comprehensive lunar calculations including phase angles, illumination, quarter searches, libration data, and node crossings."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Phase Angle","anchor":"Phase-Angle","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The phase angle indicates the Moon’s position in its cycle:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","print(\"Phase angle: \\(angle)°\")","\/\/ 0° = New Moon, 90° = First Quarter, 180° = Full, 270° = Third Quarter"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Phase Names and Emoji","anchor":"Phase-Names-and-Emoji","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Convert angles to human-readable descriptions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","","print(Moon.phaseName(for: angle))  \/\/ \"Waxing Gibbous\"","print(Moon.emoji(for: angle))      \/\/ \"🌔\""],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The eight phase names:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"New Moon (🌑)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Waxing Crescent (🌒)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"First Quarter (🌓)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Waxing Gibbous (🌔)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Full Moon (🌕)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Waning Gibbous (🌖)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Third Quarter (🌗)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Waning Crescent (🌘)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Illumination","anchor":"Illumination","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calculate the fraction of the Moon that’s lit:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","let illumination = Moon.illumination(for: angle)","print(\"Moon is \\(Int(illumination * 100))% illuminated\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Finding Quarter Phases","anchor":"Finding-Quarter-Phases","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"text":"Search for a Specific Phase","anchor":"Search-for-a-Specific-Phase","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Next full moon","let fullMoon = try Moon.searchPhase(.full, after: .now)","print(\"Next full moon: \\(fullMoon)\")","","\/\/ Next new moon","let newMoon = try Moon.searchPhase(.new, after: .now)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Get the Next Quarter","anchor":"Get-the-Next-Quarter","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let quarter = try Moon.nextQuarter(after: .now)","print(\"\\(quarter.phase.emoji) \\(quarter.phase.name) at \\(quarter.time)\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"All Quarters in a Date Range","anchor":"All-Quarters-in-a-Date-Range","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let start = AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 1, day: 1)","let end = AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 2, day: 1)","","let quarters = try Moon.quarters(from: start, to: end)","for quarter in quarters {","    print(\"\\(quarter.phase.emoji) \\(quarter.time)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Lunar Position","anchor":"Lunar-Position","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"text":"Ecliptic Coordinates","anchor":"Ecliptic-Coordinates","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let position = try Moon.eclipticPosition(at: .now)","print(\"Longitude: \\(position.longitude)°\")","print(\"Latitude: \\(position.latitude)°\")","print(\"Distance: \\(position.distance) AU\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Moon State (Position and Velocity)","anchor":"Moon-State-Position-and-Velocity","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Get the Moon’s complete state vector including velocity:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let state = try Moon.geoState(at: .now)","","\/\/ Position in AU","print(\"Distance: \\(state.position.magnitude) AU\")","","\/\/ Velocity in AU\/day","let speed = sqrt(","    state.velocity.x * state.velocity.x +","    state.velocity.y * state.velocity.y +","    state.velocity.z * state.velocity.z",")","print(\"Speed: \\(speed) AU\/day\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"code":"geoState(at:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for velocity calculations instead of differencing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ecliptic longitude positions, which gives inaccurate results.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Tip","style":"tip","type":"aside"},{"text":"Using CelestialBody","anchor":"Using-CelestialBody","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Moon is also available as a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/CelestialBody"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let horizon = try CelestialBody.moon.horizon(at: .now, from: observer)","let equatorial = try CelestialBody.moon.equatorial(at: .now)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Libration","anchor":"Libration","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Libration is the Moon’s apparent wobble that lets us see slightly more than 50% of its surface:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let lib = Moon.libration(at: .now)","","\/\/ Sub-Earth point (what's at the center of the visible disc)","print(\"Latitude: \\(lib.subEarthLatitude)°\")","print(\"Longitude: \\(lib.subEarthLongitude)°\")","","\/\/ Distance and apparent size","print(\"Distance: \\(Int(lib.distanceKM)) km\")","print(\"Apparent diameter: \\(lib.apparentDiameter)°\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Interpret libration values:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Positive latitude: More of the north polar region is visible"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Positive longitude: More of the Moon’s east limb is visible"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Lunar Nodes","anchor":"Lunar-Nodes","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The nodes are where the Moon’s orbit crosses the ecliptic plane:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Find next node crossing","let node = try Moon.searchNode(after: .now)","print(\"\\(node.kind.symbol) \\(node.kind.name) at \\(node.time)\")","\/\/ Output: \"☊ Ascending Node at 2025-01-15...\""],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Node Types","anchor":"Node-Types","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ascending (☊)","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Moon crosses from south to north of the ecliptic"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Descending (☋)"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Moon crosses from north to south"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"All Nodes in a Range","anchor":"All-Nodes-in-a-Range","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let nodes = try Moon.nodeCrossings(","    from: AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 1, day: 1),","    to: AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 12, day: 31)",")","for node in nodes {","    print(\"\\(node.kind.symbol) \\(node.time)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Lunar Apsis","anchor":"Lunar-Apsis","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Find perigee (closest) and apogee (farthest) points:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let apsis = try Moon.searchApsis(after: .now)","print(\"\\(apsis.kind.lunarName): \\(Int(apsis.distanceKM)) km\")","\/\/ Output: \"Perigee: 356,500 km\""],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"All Apsides in a Range","anchor":"All-Apsides-in-a-Range","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let apsides = try Moon.apsides(","    from: .now,","    to: .now.addingDays(60)",")","for apsis in apsides {","    print(\"\\(apsis.kind.lunarName) at \\(apsis.time)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Moonrise and Moonset","anchor":"Moonrise-and-Moonset","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/CelestialBody","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" interface:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let observer = Observer(latitude: 40.7, longitude: -74.0)","","if let moonrise = try CelestialBody.moon.riseTime(after: .now, from: observer) {","    print(\"Moonrise: \\(moonrise)\")","}","","if let moonset = try CelestialBody.moon.setTime(after: .now, from: observer) {","    print(\"Moonset: \\(moonset)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit"]]},"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Moon","anchor":"Moon","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Astronomy